  "text": "To measure bedtime procrastination, we created a state version of the bedtime procrastination scale (BPS; [CITATION_1] . Whereas the BPS asks people to report whether they generally engage in bedtime procrastination (examples include: \"I go to bed later than intended\"; \"Often, I am still doing other things when it is time to go to bed\"), the state version asks participants to report whether they engaged in bedtime procrastination in a specific time period -in this case, yesterday (example items: \"Yesterday, I went to bed later than I had intended\"; \"Yesterday, I was still doing other things when it was time to go to bed\"). The scale comprised nine items that had high inter-item reliability (α = 0.94). Items were measured on a 7-point scale (completely false-completely true); on average, participants' BPS-score was 3.37 (SD = 1.71).",
